<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        .box {
            padding: 20px;          
            border: 5px solid ; 
            margin: 10px;          
            width: 200px;         
            box-sizing: content-box;
            background-color: yellow;
        }
        h2 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }

        .border-box {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        .description {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: brown;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
    </style>
    <title>Brief Demonstration of Box Model</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>CSS Box Model Demonstration</h2>
    <div class="box">
        <p>The property is set to <strong>content-box</strong> which is also a Default representation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box border-box">
        <p>This setup uses <strong>border-box</strong> representation.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="description">
        In the <strong>content-box</strong> model, which is default setting too, represents how the box model works  when the conten's dimensions are specified. 
        <br><br>
        In the <strong>border-box</strong> model, simplifying layout representaion as dimensions are given.
    </p>
</body>
</html>


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
        margin: 20px;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            
        }

        .flex-container {
            display: flex;
            height: 200px; 
            justify-content: space-around;       
            align-items: center;                                       
            background-color: ghostwhite;          
            border: 2px solid #ccc;             
        }

        .item {
            background-color: teal;       
            flex: 1; 
            padding: 20px;                      
            margin: 10px;                       
            border-radius: 5px;                  
            text-align: center;                  
        }
        h2 {
            text-align: center;
            color: cadetblue;
        }
    </style>
    <title>Flexbox Basics</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Flexbox Layout Example:</h2>
    <div class="flex-container">
        <div class="item">Content 1</div>
        <div class="item">Content 2</div>
        <div class="item">Content 3</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: ghostwhite; 

        .main-container {
            display: flex;                      
            flex-wrap: wrap;                    
            justify-content: space-around;      
            margin-bottom: 20px;               
        }

        .card {
            background-color: lightcyan;      
            padding: 20px;                     
            margin: 10px;                      
            border-radius: 5px;                
            width: 250px;                      
            display: flex;                     
            flex-direction: column;             
            justify-content: space-between;     
        }

        .card-title {
            font-size: 1.5em;                   
            color: darkslategray;                        
        }

        .card-content {
            flex-grow: 1;                       
            color: #333;                        
        }

        .card-footer {
            text-align: center;                 
            color: darlslategray;                        
        }

        h2 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
    </style>
    <title>Advanced Flexbox Layout</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Advanced Flexbox Layout as in Example</h2>
    <div class="main-container">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">1</div>
            <div class="card-content">Respective content for the first card block.</div>
            <div class="card-footer">Footer 1</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">2</div>
            <div class="card-content">Content for card 2.</div>
            <div class="card-footer">Footer 2</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">3</div>
            <div class="card-content">Content for card 3.</div>
            <div class="card-footer">Footer 3</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">4</div>
            <div class="card-content">This card is having a longer piece of content.</div>
            <div class="card-footer">Footer 4</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
